This paper focuses on the measurement and analysis of Internet traffic, specifically VBR traffic over UDP in 802.11g and GPRS networks. This topic falls under the sub-category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of transmission delay on round trip delay, which could also fall under the sub-category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) as it relates to network security. The paper also mentions the use of mobile devices, which could fall under the sub-category of Multimedia (cs.MM) as mobile devices are often used for multimedia applications. The paper also presents numerical parameters for distribution, which could fall under the sub-categories of Information Theory (cs.IT) or Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
